## 8. Reporting
POA&M status (open, overdue, closed; trend on on-time closure rate per `security-metrics-and-objectives.md.template`) is reported to the Steering Committee at each meeting and to management review. The register is provided to external assessors as evidence of remediation discipline.

## 9. Exceptions
Where a finding cannot be remediated within target and the residual risk is accepted, the deferral is recorded as a time-bound exception per `exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved at the appropriate level, and cross-referenced from the POA&M item.

## 10. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The completeness and accuracy of the register are verified at internal audit and management review. Owners are accountable for timely remediation; chronic overdue items are escalated to leadership and may factor into performance management per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

